{"word":"H567 - אֱמֹרִי - ʼĔmôrîy - em-o-ree' - Amorite","slug":"H567","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אֱמֹרִי</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼĔmôrîy"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>em-o-ree'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Amorite"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>אמרי</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>'ĕmôrı̂y</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>em-o-ree'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Amorite = \"a sayer\" <ol><li>one of the peoples of east Canaan and beyond the Jordan, dispossessed by the Israelite incursion from Egypt</li></ol> <p />Origin: probably a patronymic from an unused name derived from <a href=\"#/H559\">H559</a> in the sense of publicity, i.e. prominence <p />TWOT entry: <a class=\"T\" href=\"S:0119 - 'emori\">119</a> <p />Part(s) of speech: Noun Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H201\">H201</a>, <a href=\"#/H204\">H204</a>, <a href=\"#/H3982\">H3982</a>, <a href=\"#/H534\">H534</a>, <a href=\"#/H559\">H559</a>, <a href=\"#/H561\">H561</a>, <a href=\"#/H562\">H562</a>, <a href=\"#/H564\">H564</a>, <a href=\"#/H565\">H565</a>, <a href=\"#/H566\">H566</a>, <a href=\"#/H568\">H568</a>, <a href=\"#/H569\">H569</a>, <a href=\"#/H570\">H570</a>, <a href=\"#/H577\">H577</a>"}]}